// useDesignHistory
// Fetches and exposes the version history for a single design, with abort-safe loading.

History is re-fetched whenever designId, project, or session changes.
Fetch requests are aborted via AbortController if the designId changes before the response arrives.
A staleness check on designIdRef guards against out-of-order responses.

FUNCTION useDesignHistory(designId) -> { history, isLoading, error, refetch, getVersionAt }  EXPORT
  CALLS: useSession (useSession), api (api)
  Manages state: history, isLoading, error.
  On mount (and when designId changes), fires fetchHistory with an AbortSignal; aborts on cleanup.
  IF designId is null, clears history immediately.

---

FUNCTION fetchHistory(signal?)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Fetches the history for the current designId from the API.
  Skips if designId, project, or session are absent.
  Ignores AbortError and responses that arrive after designId has changed.
  On success, stores the history data. On network error, sets error to "Network error".

---

FUNCTION getVersionAt(timestamp) -> string | null
  CALLS: api (api)
  Fetches the design content at a specific timestamp.
  Returns the content string on success, or null if the request fails or context is missing.
